<item>
            <title>[TIKA-295] Rough cut of mbox parser</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-295</link>
                <project id="12310631" key="TIKA">Tika</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Attached is a patch for a first-cut at a parser that handles mailbox (.mbox, application/mbox) files.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The first email headers are used to fill in metadata. Subsequent email headers are tossed.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Charset handling needs to be fixed up. It&apos;s unclear (not spec&apos;d) whether emails individually use the charset as specified in their individual header, or the entire file should be re-encoded (and the encoding is sent in the response header, or auto-detected).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Multi-part emails won&apos;t be handled properly, though it&apos;s unclear what should be done in that case (if anything).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
